  "prompt": "What are the best restaurants to try when visiting Hubbali, Karnataka, India? What should you try while you're there?",
  "response": "Hubli (or Hubballi) is a vibrant city in Karnataka, India, known for its rich culture and delicious cuisine. Here are some of the best restaurants to try and the must-have dishes while you're there:\n\n---\n\n### **Top Restaurants in Hubli**\n1. **Durgamba Hotel**  \n   - Famous for its authentic North Karnataka meals, especially **Jowar Roti**, **Ennegai**, and **Shenga chutney**.\n   - A great place to experience local flavors.\n\n2. **Kamat Yatrinivas**  \n   - Known for its traditional South Indian thali and Karnataka specialties like **Benne Dosa** (butter dosa) and **Holige** (sweet flatbread).\n\n3. **Udupi Garden**  \n   - A popular vegetarian restaurant offering South Indian delicacies like **Masala Dosa**, **Idli-Vada**, and **Kesari Bath**.\n\n4. **Nandan Restaurant**  \n   - Famous for its North Karnataka thali and **Jolada Roti** with **Brinjal curry** and **Buttermilk**.\n\n5. **Kundan Sweets**  \n   - A must-visit for sweets and snacks like **Mysore Pak**, **Kaju Katli**, and **Chakli**.\n\n6. **Hotel Mappila**  \n   - Known for its Kerala-style cuisine, especially **Appam** and **Stew**.\n\n7. **Arya Bhavan**  \n   - Offers a mix of North and South Indian dishes, including **Pav Bhaji** and **Rava Idli**.\n\n8. **Krishna Garden**  \n   - A great spot for North Indian and Chinese cuisine, along with local Karnataka dishes.\n\n---\n\n### **Must-Try Dishes in Hubli**\n1. **Benne Dosa** - A crispy, buttery dosa that is a Karnataka specialty.\n2. **Jolada Roti with Ennegai** - A traditional flatbread made of jowar (sorghum) served with stuffed brinjal curry.\n3. **Shenga Chutney** - A flavorful peanut-based chutney often served with jowar roti.\n4. **Holige** - A sweet flatbread stuffed with jaggery and lentils or coconut.\n5. **Ragi Mudde** - A nutritious Kannada staple made with finger millet, served with spicy curries.\n6. **Bisi Bele Bath** - A spicy and tangy rice dish with lentils and vegetables.\n7. **Churmuri** - A popular street food snack made with puffed rice, spices, and vegetables.\n8. **Pathrode** - A steamed dish made with colocasia leaves and a spiced rice paste.\n\n---\n\n### **Pro Tips**\n- Don\u2019t miss out on trying fresh **Filter Coffee** at local cafes.\n- Explore street food stalls for **Kachori**, **Samosa**, and **Mirchi Bajji**.\n- Hubli is also famous for its **Mango Pickles** and **Papads**, which make great souvenirs.\n\nEnjoy your culinary adventure in Hubli!",
